race.comment: TAIPAN LEGEND (8) had a five-week break prior to his effortless win in a Class 3 over the mile at Coonamble last start. Tackling a deeper field today but he drops 3kgs and is rock hard fit. Will give them something to catch. OCEANFRONT (7) was a month between runs before his barnstorming win over 1850m at this track recently. Up in class but capable of taking that step. MORNING SUN (2) showed a glimpse of form last start when close up at Warwick Farm over the mile. Has taken a while to fire this campaign but he looks ready to peak now. CLAIM THE CROWN (3) is fitter for three runs back from a spell and on his best form can trouble a field of this quality.
